metadata.name: Sa·πÖkhƒÅra #2
metadata.description:
üéß CLICK/TAP FOR SOUND ON

Sa·πÖkhƒÅra is a portrait of symbolic consciousness in three movements.

Colorful automata represents direct experience: touch, sight, hearing, smell, taste and thought in a ceaseless flow of novelty.

The automata congeals into form alluding to the way our minds close over experience with symbolic representation, like a plastic bag coming down over a kaleidoscope of butterflies. What was free in the open air is now trapped. What was previously wild and unpredictable is now under control, frozen and communicable.

The form‚Äôs dispersal mimics the release of mental formation, the unbinding of a symbol, the letting go of a belief. It‚Äôs a visceral reflection of the process of ceasing to identify with separateness. To strain the previous metaphor, it‚Äôs the opening of the bag and letting the butterflies return to the flow of raw, boundless experience.

‚Äî

K.C. Austin
From his cockpit in the Blue Ridge Mountains K.C. Austin (aka bzor) spends his days shaping realtime software art systems of all stripes. Informed by game design, modular synths, virtual reality and consciousness research, K.C. plays shaders like a fiddle and fashions creative pipelines like a spider spins webs.

James Paterson
Fascinated by the relationship between ancient and futuristic mediums, James Paterson has been exploring a unique synthesis of drawing, code, animation and sculpture under the moniker ‚ÄòPresstube‚Äô since 1999. Paterson draws inspiration from meditation, molecular biology, music, parenting and psychedelics - the seen, the heard, the felt, the cognized.

metadata.name: The City #236
metadata.description:
// The City //

Cities are the most complex human-made interventions on Earth. The human settlements are growing like huge organisms ‚Äì and the growth is often impossible to plan, control or limit.
Cities as a phenomenon are with their incredible complexity highly enigmatic structures, that are as fascinating as they are terrifying.

This project is a study of the beauty of complexity.

Each city iteration is an entirely unique structure with unique hatching, arrangement of buildings, heights, sizes, additions and rare items.
The cities are made even more organic by the meticulous modelling of analog ink drawing.

The project is 100% generative. All lines, hatching and dots are generated for each iteration.

As a gesture of appreciation towards our supporters, 20% of royalties will go to the original minter.

Key commands:
Press 's' to save a png version
Press '2' to render at twice the resolution
Press 'b' to remove the colored background before saving

The loading progress is animated, hence the epileptic trigger warning.
Due to memory constraints on mobile devices, rendering uses a lower resolution on these.
-----------

Original concept by @Lax_raven
All code by @r1b2art

metadata.name: Primordial #47
metadata.description:
Primordial is a study of abstract forms. The algorithm, written in p5.js and WebGL, utilizes domain warping to create twisted fields of color and then overlays thousands of tiny lines to provide depth and texture. The outputs are chaotic but not completely formless, like a swirling mass of plasma from the early universe, or a strange proto-life form suspended in prehistoric ooze.

CONTROLS:

1-9: Increase resolution and save image in PNG format

B: Toggle borders on/off

F: Fullscreen
P: Portrait
L: Landscape
S: Square

For third party license information, please see license.md

David Brice Allen
October 2022

metadata.name: NOMADS #4
metadata.description:
NOMADS tells a story through each of its editions: the migration of a population, following simple rules, and whose movements reveal complex shapes and textures, both visual and auditory.
Movement, order, chaos, borders, convergence, wandering, rotation... it's all part of NOMADS

Enjoy the journey as much as the destination


KEYBOARD SHORCUTS:
[S]: Redraw the art and save a 4K PNG
[L]: Toggle between "Infinite Loop" and "Single Render" modes
[M]: Toggle mute

MOUSE / TOUCHSCREEN:
[Click / Tap]: Toggle mute
[Double Click / Double Tap]: Save the current render

URL PARAMETERS:
?start : bypass the intro timer and start the rendering
?loop : select the "Infinite Loop" mode by default
?resolution=1920x1080 : render in a custom resolution using the format WIDTHxHEIGHT. Different aspect ratios will produce different results.
?frame=0.1 : control the frame size around the canvas (value between 0 and 1)
?save : automatically save the image when the rendering is done


Artist: Estienne
Oct. 2022
NFT 2.0 License

Best viewed on Chrome or Chromium based browser
Tested on Chrome v 106.0.5249.119

Libraries used:
p5.js
Tone.js

metadata.name: BRUTALIST MOVEMENT #9
metadata.description:
Inspired and fascinated by Brutalism, Modernism and Bauhaus, I've started to explore the deeper connections of architecture using pixel art in a clean, minimalistic and unique way.

The BRUTALIST MOVEMENT project represents the next step in this process. It's an animated generative experiment that focuses on finding the simplest and fewest components that - when generated randomly - always create structures resembling buildings: from small modern houses through industrial facilities to gigantic brutalist monuments.

This resulted in 4 main components: Base, Extension, Gap and Window. These entities are used randomly to create Blocks that form the final structure. 
The whole process is also strictly accompanied by 4 distinct components to hold colors and to be set by randomly chosen palettes: Sky, Sun, Shadow, Window.

Features consist of a mixture of the above components.

The project is animated to show how the buildings come to life. It's also a nice way to show what's going on in the background, because from time to time a bigger block would surely hide interesting smaller ones :) 

Press these keys:
's' - to download a larger resolution PNG
'n' - to shuffle through the 'depth' of Blocks, aka placing them from front to back and vice versa. This is a nice feature to show structures hidden by others and also a cool way to create iterations inside the iteration - sub-iterations - we can say :)
'r' - to reset the Blocks' depths to default

Please note:
Everything you see is generated, animated and drawn real-time. No layered transparent PNGs, PFP or similar!

Have fun and inspiration!


@cloudnoise ¬© 2022
